  "text": "A study by Van Staa et al. [CITATION_1] evaluated the ageand gender-specific incidence of PDB in England and Wales in the adult population. They concluded that the disorder was more frequent among men of all ages over 55 years. The incidence increased steeply with age among both men and women, and was estimated at 0.3 cases per 10,000 person-years among women aged 55-59 years and 0.5 cases per 10,000 person-years among men of similar age. At the age of ≥85 years, this rate rose to 5.4 among women and 7.6 among men. Based on these assumptions, the prevalence of clinically diagnosed PDB is 0.3 % among men and women ≥55 years old.",
